examples.en: He stared at her severely.
The fall severely damaged her knee.
The car went into a tree and was severely damaged.
Several of the passengers were severely injured in the accident.
No one was hurt, but many of the passengers were severely shaken up.
Tom's latest book has been severely put down in the newspaper reports.
If you perjure yourself you will be severely punished.
He suffered a severe head injury.
In the most severe cases, the disease can lead to blindness.
The new drug is being tested on a group of severely depressed patients.
He is on a severely restricted diet.
Press freedom is severely restricted.
I fell on the gravel, severely grazing my knee.
I turned a corner to find the road ahead severely flooded.
She was severely affected by the bank's failure.
The original scope of the work had been severely reduced.
It grieved me to learn that she had been severely injured.
Under  military regime, civil liberties may be severely curtailed.
The children were severely trounced.
If you do that again you will be severely punished. Do I make myself plain?
He promised to punish severely any officials found guilty of electoral fraud.
The cramped living conditions severely restricted the children's freedom to play.
After a night spent partying, the fraternity brothers were all severely inebriated.
Women's employment opportunities are often severely constrained by family commitments.
